# ANTI-SLOP STANDARD RULES (Cursor)

## PRINCIPLES
- Nothing redundant, generic, or purposeless.
- Eliminate slop: obvious comments, dead code, duplication.
- Comments only explain the "why".
- Do not invent APIs, structures, or concepts foreign to the code.

## MODES AND COMMANDS
anti-slop check <path>       # non-destructive inspection
anti-slop apply <path>       # applies safe fixes
anti-slop validate <path>    # validates types, routes, schemas

Flags:
--mode normal | backend | frontend | design
--auto-apply
--dry-run

## BACKEND RULES
- Clean and non-duplicated REST routes.
- A single HTTP client and a single DB client.
- Handlers <10 lines; logic in services.
- Mandatory Zod validation.
- Errors with uniform structure.
- ENV validated at startup.

## FRONTEND TECH RULES
- Server Components by default.
- `use client` only if essential.
- Tailwind without arbitrary classes.
- Images with width/height; lazy loading.
- Goals: LCP≤2.5s, INP≤200ms, CLS≤0.1.
- Accessibility: contrast ≥4.5.

## DESIGN RULES
- Colors only from tokens.
- Do not hardcode hex.
- Non-generic fonts without justification.
- Maximum 1–2 animations per view.

## PR RULES
- Destructive changes require human PR.
- API, DB, AUTH contracts or tokens require mandatory review.
